  41,50,Ac when nos beatus eum suffering some adversity he dictus Hoc belongs to me. Ego non believe Hora ever advenit pass Et si ego returned my Dominus ego invenit Eum bene things. Multus certainly nos inform disbelievers de totus their works commit them severe retribution
  41,51,When nos beatus human est he turns drifts farther farther away when he suffers any affliction he implores loudly
  41,52,Proclaim Quod hoc est enim ex DEUS tunc vos decide reject it Qui est farther astray than those decide oppose hoc
  41,53,Nos show them noster proofs horizons intra dum they realize ut hoc est truth. est tuus Dominus non sufficient testis totus things
